# Windsurf Rules

## AI Configuration

This project uses `.ai/` as the single source of truth for AI behavior.
Always read and follow the guidelines in:

- `.ai/skills/` — Coding best practices, patterns, and playbooks
- `.ai/rules/` — Hard constraints and conventions (always follow these)
- `.ai/agents/` — Specialized AI personas for specific tasks
- `.ai/commands/` — Reusable command templates and macros
- `.ai/prompts/` — Pre-built prompt templates

## Instructions

Read `SPEC.md` for project facts, stack, and key invariants.
Load `docs/spec/<feature>/SPEC.md` when the user's task mentions that feature.
Read all files in `.ai/rules/` first — hard constraints, never violate.
Load `.ai/skills/<name>/` when the topic matches.
Command templates in `.ai/commands/` — use when the user references one by name.
